Moody's Investors Service Inc said itmay downgrade 1.3 billion dlrs of debt of Public ServiceCompany of New Hampshire.    Under review are B-1 first mortgage bonds, B-2 refundingmortgage bonds, B-3 third mortgage and secured pollutioncontrol revenue bonds, Caa debentures and preferred stock.    Moody's cited an uncertain ability to meet fixed-incomeobligations due to the Nuclear Regulatory Commission's refusalto grant a low-power operating license because of inadequateevacuation plans. The firm depends on credit markets to fundobligations, due to a negative internal cash flow, it said. Reuter&#3;